        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 5:12PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Reese Center, or 11 miles west of Lubbock, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lubbock, Wolfforth, Shallowater, Lubbock International Airport, Texas
Tech University, Downtown Lubbock, Lubbock South Plains Mall, Reese
Center, New Deal, and Smyer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
